{"title_page": "Spiral (2021 film)", "text_new": "{{short description|Upcoming horror film directed by Darren Lynn Bousman}}\n{{Use American English|date=April 2020}}\n{{Use mdy dates|date=April 2020}}\n{{Infobox film\n| name           = Spiral: From The Book of Saw\n| image          = Spiral (2020) poster.jpeg\n| border         = no\n| caption        = Teaser poster with original release date\n| director       = [[Darren Lynn Bousman]]\n| producer       = {{Plainlist|\n* [[Oren Koules]]\n* [[Mark Burg]]\n}}\n| screenplay     = {{Plainlist|\n* [[Josh Stolberg]]\n* Peter Goldfinger\n}}\n| story          = [[Chris Rock]]\n| starring       = {{Plainlist|\n* Chris Rock\n* [[Samuel L. Jackson]]\n}}\n| music          = [[Charlie Clouser]]\n| cinematography = Jordan Oram<ref>{{cite web |url=https://hnentertainment.co/new-rumor-suggests-spider-man-far-from-home-star-samuel-l-jackson-has-joined-chris-rocks-saw-reboot/ |title=Update: 'Spider-Man: Far From Home' Star Samuel L. Jackson Has Joined Chris Rock's 'Saw' Reboot |last=Marc |first=Christopher |website=HN Entertainment |date=July 8, 2019 |accessdate=November 2, 2019}}</ref>\n| editing        = Dev Singh<ref>{{cite web |last=Singh |first=Dev |title=Dev Singh Biography |url=https://www.dgc.ca/en/national/the-guild/leaders/national-directors-division/memberView?m=22606 |website=Directors Guild of Canada |accessdate=November 2, 2019}}</ref>\n| studio         = [[Twisted Pictures]]\n| distributor    = {{Plainlist|\n* [[Lionsgate Films|Lionsgate]] (United States)\n* [[Mongrel Media]] (Canada)\n}}\n| released       = {{Film date|2021|5|21|United States}}\n| runtime        = \n| country        = United States\n| language       = English\n| budget         = \n| gross          = \n}}\n\n'''''Spiral: From The Book of Saw''''', or simply '''''Spiral''''', is an upcoming American [[horror film|horror]] film directed by [[Darren Lynn Bousman]], written by [[Josh Stolberg]] and Peter Goldfinger, based on a story by [[Chris Rock]]. It is the ninth installment in the [[Saw (franchise)|''Saw'' film series]] and stars Rock, [[Samuel L. Jackson]], [[Max Minghella]], and [[Marisol Nichols]].\n\nThe film is scheduled to be released in the United States on May 21, 2021, by [[Lionsgate Films|Lionsgate]], after being delayed from its original release date of  May 15, 2020, due to the [[COVID-19 pandemic]].<ref name=\"Reschedule\">{{cite web |url=https://collider.com/new-saw-movie-spiral-antebellum-release-date-delayed-coronavirus/ |title=Lionsgate Delays Chris Rock's 'Saw' Movie, Janelle Monae's 'Antebellum' |website=[[Collider (website)|Collider]] |first=Jeff |last=Sneider |date=March 17, 2020 |accessdate=March 17, 2020}}</ref><ref name=\"NewDate\">{{cite web |url=https://variety.com/2020/film/news/lionsgate-hitmans-wifes-bodyguard-john-wick-chapter-4-1234595835/ |title='John Wick: Chapter 4,' 'The Hitman's Wife's Bodyguard' Get New Release Dates |website=[[Variety (website)|Variety]] |first=Dave |last=McNary |date=May 1, 2020 |accessdate=May 1, 2020}}</ref>\n\n== Synopsis ==\nLionsgate's officially released synopsis reads \"Working in the shadow of an esteemed police veteran ([[Samuel L. Jackson]]), brash detective Ezekiel \"Zeke\" Banks ([[Chris Rock]]) and his rookie partner William Schenk ([[Max Minghella]]) take charge of a grisly investigation into murders that are eerily reminiscent of the city's gruesome past. Unwittingly trapped in a deepening mystery, Zeke finds himself at the center of the killer's morbid game.\"<ref name=\"Patches\"/>\n\n== Cast ==\n{{Details|topic=the cast and characters|List of Saw cast members|List of Saw characters}}\n* [[Chris Rock]] as Det. Ezekiel \"Zeke\" Banks<ref name=\"thewrap\"/>\n* [[Samuel L. Jackson]] as Marcus Banks<ref name=\"thewrap\"/>\n* [[Max Minghella]] as Det. William Schenk<ref name=\"thewrap\">{{cite web |url=https://www.thewrap.com/samuel-l-jackson-joins-chris-rocks-saw-reboot/ |title=Samuel L. Jackson Joins Chris Rock's 'Saw' Reboot |last=Welk |first=Brian |website=[[TheWrap]] |date=July 8, 2019 |accessdate=July 8, 2019}}</ref>\n* [[Marisol Nichols]] as Captain Angie Garza<ref name=\"thewrap\"/>\n* [[Zoie Palmer]] as Kara Boswick<ref>{{cite web |title=Spiral: From the Book of Saw |url=http://www.mongrelmedia.com/index.php/filmlink?id=66364d59-dfc5-e911-a98f-0edcbcd33718 |website=[[Mongrel Media]] |date=2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |title=First poster for Saw reboot Spiral is here! |url=https://moviehole.net/first-poster-for-saw-reboot-spiral-is-here/ |author=Editorial Staff |website=Moviehole |date=February 5, 2020 |accessdate=April 18, 2020}}</ref>\n\n== Production ==\n=== Development ===\nAccording to [[Chris Rock]], the origins of ''Spiral: From The Book of Saw'' came from a chance meeting with the head of [[Lionsgate Films|Lionsgate]] at a friend's wedding, and felt doing something in the horror genre would be a new avenue to take his career, though planned to include some comedic elements in the film.<ref>{{cite web | url = https://collider.com/why-chris-rock-made-a-saw-movie/ | title = Chris Rock Explains Why He Made a 'Saw' Movie | first = Adam | last =Chitwood | date = January 13, 2020 | accessdate = January 22, 2020 | work = [[Collider (website)|Collider]] }}</ref>  Rock approached Lionsgate with his ideas of extending the franchise, who became very interested in the concept.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://deadline.com/2019/05/chris-rock-to-reboot-saw-franchise-with-lionsgate-twisted-pictures-1202616185/ |title=Chris Rock To Reboot 'Saw' Franchise With Lionsgate & Twisted Pictures |website=[[Deadline Hollywood]] |publisher=[[Penske Media Corporation]] |first=Anthony |last=D'Alessandro |date=May 16, 2019 |accessdate=August 31, 2019}}</ref> Lionsgate's CEO [[Joe Drake (producer)|Joe Drake]] said that Rock's idea was \"completely reverential to the legacy of the material while reinvigorating the brand with his wit, creative vision and passion for this classic horror franchise\".<ref name=\"announce\"/> By January 2018, industry rumors had said that Lionsgate had begun discussions of a ninth ''Saw'' film, for which [[The Spierig Brothers]] would not be returning.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://screenrant.com/saw-9-jigsaw-sequel/ |title='Saw 9' Conversation is Reportedly Happening |last=Stephens |first=David |website=[[Screen Rant]] |publisher=Valnet, Inc. |date=January 16, 2018 |accessdate=July 8, 2019}}</ref> By April 2018, [[Twisted Pictures]] was reported to be developing a sequel with ''[[Jigsaw (2017 film)|Jigsaw]]'' writers [[Josh Stolberg]] and Peter Goldfinger.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://bloody-disgusting.com/movie/3491755/jigsaw-writers-currently-working-next-saw-exclusive/ |title='Jigsaw' Writers Are Currently Working On Next 'Saw' [Exclusive] |last=Miska |first=Brad |website=[[Bloody Disgusting]] |date=April 3, 2018 |accessdate=July 8, 2019}}</ref>\n\nOn May 16, 2019, the film was officially in production.<ref name=\"announce\"/> Former series director [[Darren Lynn Bousman]] returned to helm the film, along with series veterans [[Mark Burg]] and [[Oren Koules]] as producers. Rock was involved as an executive producer, in addition to writing the story treatment. Joining Rock as executive producers included the original ''[[Saw (2004 film)|Saw]]'' creators [[James Wan]] and [[Leigh Whannell]], along with Daniel Heffner.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://bloody-disgusting.com/movie/3561412/saw-reimagined-chris-rock-darren-bousman-returning-direct/ |title='Saw' Being Reimagined by Chris Rock with Darren Bousman Returning to Direct! |first=Brad |last=Miska |website=[[Bloody Disgusting]] |date=May 16, 2019 |accessdate=August 31, 2019}}</ref> Stolberg and Goldfinger were affirmed as scriptwriters.<ref name=\"announce\"/> With the announcement, Rock stated, \"I've been a fan of ''Saw'' since the first film in 2004. I am excited by the opportunity to take this to a really intense and twisted new place.\"<ref name=\"announce\">{{cite web | url = https://variety.com/2019/film/news/chris-rock-saw-spinoff-1203216731/ | title = Chris Rock Rebooting 'Saw' Franchise With Lionsgate | first=  Dave | last =  McNary | date = May 16, 2019 | accessdate = July 8, 2019 | work = [[Variety (magazine)|Variety]] | publisher = [[Penske Media Corporation]] }}</ref> Burg and Koules said that Rock's treatment of ''Saw'' was comparable to what [[Eddie Murphy]] had done for [[buddy cop film]]s in ''[[48 Hrs.]]'', giving the ''Saw'' series a \"completely fresh perspective\".<ref name=\"announce\"/> Stolberg later confirmed that the ninth installment will exist in the same canon as the previous eight films, and will not be a reboot, nor will it be a direct sequel to ''Jigsaw''.<ref>{{cite web | url = https://www.digitalspy.com/movies/a28205256/saw-movie-reboot-timeline-confirmed/ | title = How 'Saw' reboot fits in with the series timeline | first= Dan | last = Seddon | date = July 8, 2019 | accessdate = July 8, 2019 | work = [[Digital Spy]] | publisher = [[Hearst Communications]]}}</ref>\n\n=== Filming ===\nOn July 8, 2019, filming commenced in [[Toronto]] under the working title of ''The Organ Donor''. Rock, [[Samuel L. Jackson]], [[Max Minghella]] and [[Marisol Nichols]] were announced to be starring in the film.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://variety.com/2019/film/news/samuel-l-jackson-chris-rock-saw-movie-1203260924/ |title=Samuel L. Jackson to Star in Chris Rock's 'Saw' Reboot |last=McNary |first=Dave |date=July 8, 2019 |website=[[Variety (magazine)|Variety]] |publisher=[[Penske Media Corporation]] |accessdate=July 8, 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://screenrant.com/saw-9-movie-filming-start/ |title=New 'Saw' Movie Set To Start Filming This Month |website=[[Screen Rant]] |publisher=Valnet, Inc. |first=Q. V. |last=Hough |date=June 27, 2019 |accessdate=August 31, 2019}}</ref> Lionsgate's CEO Joe Drake stated, \"We think Samuel L. Jackson and Chris Rock along with Max Minghella and Marisol Nichols make this film completely special in the ''Saw'' canon and we can't wait to unleash this unexpected and sinister new story on fans of this franchise. This is next level of ''Saw'' on full tilt.\"<ref>{{cite web |url=https://io9.gizmodo.com/more-like-saw-muel-l-jackson-right-1836185124?IR=T |title=More Like Saw-muel L. Jackson, Right? |last=Lussier |first=Germain |date=July 9, 2019 |website=[[Gizmodo]] |publisher=[[G/O Media]] |accessdate=July 8, 2019}}</ref> On August 28, 2019, filming officially wrapped.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://bloody-disgusting.com/movie/3580945/chris-rocks-new-take-saw-wraps-production/ |title=Chris Rock's New Take on 'Saw' Wraps Production |last=Brad |first=Miska |date=August 28, 2019 |website=[[Bloody Disgusting]] |accessdate=August 29, 2019}}</ref> In February 2020, the [[Motion Picture Association of America]] gave the film an R rating, for \"sequences of grisly bloody violence and torture, pervasive language, some sexual references and brief drug use\".<ref>{{cite web | url=https://www.filmratings.com/Search?filmTitle=spiral&x=0&y=0| title=Spiral (2020) | work=The Classification and Rating Adiministration | publisher=[[Motion Picture Association of America]] | accessdate=February 26, 2020}}</ref>\n\n== Marketing ==\nThe film was known under the working title ''The Organ Donor''<ref>{{cite web |last=Wilhelmi |first=Jack |title=How Does The 'Saw' Reboot Connect To The Original Movies? |url=https://screenrant.com/how-the-saw-reboot-connects-to-original-movies/ |website=[[Screen Rant]] |date=November 24, 2019 |accessdate=March 21, 2020}}</ref> until the name ''Spiral: From the Book of Saw'' was leaked to the press on January 22, 2020, along with [[Mongrel Media]] as the Canadian distributor.<ref>{{cite web |last=Burwick |first=Kevin |title=Bewildering 'Saw 9' Title Allegedly Leaks, But Is It for Real? |url=https://movieweb.com/saw-9-official-title-spiral/ |website=[[MovieWeb]] |date=January 22, 2020 |accessdate=March 21, 2020}}</ref> The first teaser poster and trailer, released on February 5, 2020, confirmed ''Spiral'' as the title of the film.<ref name=\"Patches\">{{cite web |last=Patches |first= Matt |url=https://www.polygon.com/2020/2/5/21124064/spiral-trailer-chris-rock-saw-reboot|title=The 'Spiral' trailer is our first cut of Chris Rock's 'Saw' reboot|website=[[Polygon (website)|Polygon]]|publisher=[[Vox Media]]|date=February 5, 2020|accessdate = February 5, 2020}}</ref>\n\n== Release ==\n''Spiral: From The Book of Saw'' is scheduled to be released in the United States on May 21, 2021, by [[Lionsgate Films|Lionsgate]].<ref name=\"NewDate\" /> The film was originally scheduled to be released on October 23, 2020, but was moved up to May 15, 2020.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://variety.com/2019/film/news/chris-rock-saw-reboot-may-2020-1203275353/ |title=Chris Rock's 'Saw' Reboot Moves Up Five Months to May 2020 |website=[[Variety (magazine)|Variety]] |publisher=[[Penske Media Corporation]] |last=McNary |first=Dave |date=July 22, 2019 |accessdate=July 23, 2019}}</ref> The film was later delayed to its current release date, as a result of the [[COVID-19 pandemic]].<ref name=\"Reschedule\" />\n\n== See also ==\n* [[Impact of the COVID-19 pandemic on cinema]]\n\n== References ==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n== External links ==\n* {{Official website|https://www.lionsgate.com/movies/spiral}}\n* {{IMDb title|10342730|Spiral}}\n* [http://www.mongrelmedia.com/index.php/filmlink?id=66364d59-dfc5-e911-a98f-0edcbcd33718  ''Spiral''] on [[Mongrel Media]]\n\n{{Chris Rock}}\n{{Darren Lynn Bousman}}\n{{Saw}}\n{{Portal bar|Film|Speculative fiction/Horror}}\n\n[[Category:2021 horror films]]\n[[Category:2021 films]]\n[[Category:American films]]\n[[Category:American horror films]]\n[[Category:American sequel films]]\n[[Category:English-language films]]\n[[Category:Films directed by Darren Lynn Bousman]]\n[[Category:Films postponed due to the 2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic]]\n[[Category:Films shot in Toronto]]\n[[Category:Lions Gate Entertainment films]]\n[[Category:Saw films]]\n[[Category:Torture in films]]\n[[Category:Upcoming films]]\n[[Category:Upcoming sequel films]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|Upcoming horror film directed by Darren Lynn Bousman}}\n{{Use American English|date=April 2020}}\n{{Use mdy dates|date=April 2020}}\n{{Infobox film\n| name           = Spiral: From The Book of Saw\n| image          = Spiral (2020) poster.jpeg\n| border         = no\n| caption        = Teaser poster with original release date\n| director       = [[Darren Lynn Bousman]]\n| producer       = {{Plainlist|\n* [[Oren Koules]]\n* [[Mark Burg]]\n}}\n| screenplay     = {{Plainlist|\n* [[Josh Stolberg]]\n* Peter Goldfinger\n}}\n| story          = [[Chris Rock]]\n| starring       = {{Plainlist|\n* Chris Rock\n* [[Samuel L. Jackson]]\n}}\n| music          = [[Charlie Clouser]]\n| cinematography = Jordan Oram<ref>{{cite web |url=https://hnentertainment.co/new-rumor-suggests-spider-man-far-from-home-star-samuel-l-jackson-has-joined-chris-rocks-saw-reboot/ |title=Update: 'Spider-Man: Far From Home' Star Samuel L. Jackson Has Joined Chris Rock's 'Saw' Reboot |last=Marc |first=Christopher |website=HN Entertainment |date=July 8, 2019 |accessdate=November 2, 2019}}</ref>\n| editing        = Dev Singh<ref>{{cite web |last=Singh |first=Dev |title=Dev Singh Biography |url=https://www.dgc.ca/en/national/the-guild/leaders/national-directors-division/memberView?m=22606 |website=Directors Guild of Canada |accessdate=November 2, 2019}}</ref>\n| studio         = [[Twisted Pictures]]\n| distributor    = {{Plainlist|\n* [[Lionsgate Films|Lionsgate]] (United States)\n* [[Mongrel Media]] (Canada)\n}}\n| released       = {{Film date|2021|5|21|United States}}\n| runtime        = \n| country        = United States\n| language       = English\n| budget         = \n| gross          = \n}}\n\n'''''Spiral: From The Book of Saw''''', or simply '''''Spiral''''', is an upcoming American [[horror film|horror]] film directed by [[Darren Lynn Bousman]], written by [[Josh Stolberg]] and Peter Goldfinger, based on a story by [[Chris Rock]]. It is the ninth installment in the [[Saw (franchise)|''Saw'' film series]] and stars Rock, [[Samuel L. Jackson]], [[Max Minghella]], [[Marisol Nichols]] and [[Zoie Palmer]].\n\nThe film is scheduled to be released in the United States on May 21, 2021, by [[Lionsgate Films|Lionsgate]], after being delayed from its original release date of  May 15, 2020, due to the [[COVID-19 pandemic]].<ref name=\"Reschedule\">{{cite web |url=https://collider.com/new-saw-movie-spiral-antebellum-release-date-delayed-coronavirus/ |title=Lionsgate Delays Chris Rock's 'Saw' Movie, Janelle Monae's 'Antebellum' |website=[[Collider (website)|Collider]] |first=Jeff |last=Sneider |date=March 17, 2020 |accessdate=March 17, 2020}}</ref><ref name=\"NewDate\">{{cite web |url=https://variety.com/2020/film/news/lionsgate-hitmans-wifes-bodyguard-john-wick-chapter-4-1234595835/ |title='John Wick: Chapter 4,' 'The Hitman's Wife's Bodyguard' Get New Release Dates |website=[[Variety (website)|Variety]] |first=Dave |last=McNary |date=May 1, 2020 |accessdate=May 1, 2020}}</ref>\n\n== Synopsis ==\nLionsgate's officially released synopsis reads \"Working in the shadow of an esteemed police veteran ([[Samuel L. Jackson]]), brash detective Ezekiel \"Zeke\" Banks ([[Chris Rock]]) and his rookie partner William Schenk ([[Max Minghella]]) take charge of a grisly investigation into murders that are eerily reminiscent of the city's gruesome past. Unwittingly trapped in a deepening mystery, Zeke finds himself at the center of the killer's morbid game.\"<ref name=\"Patches\"/>\n\n== Cast ==\n{{Details|topic=the cast and characters|List of Saw cast members|List of Saw characters}}\n* [[Chris Rock]] as Det. Ezekiel \"Zeke\" Banks<ref name=\"thewrap\"/>\n* [[Samuel L. Jackson]] as Marcus Banks<ref name=\"thewrap\"/>\n* [[Max Minghella]] as Det. William Schenk<ref name=\"thewrap\">{{cite web |url=https://www.thewrap.com/samuel-l-jackson-joins-chris-rocks-saw-reboot/ |title=Samuel L. Jackson Joins Chris Rock's 'Saw' Reboot |last=Welk |first=Brian |website=[[TheWrap]] |date=July 8, 2019 |accessdate=July 8, 2019}}</ref>\n* [[Marisol Nichols]] as Captain Angie Garza<ref name=\"thewrap\"/>\n* [[Zoie Palmer]] as Kara Boswick<ref>{{cite web |title=Spiral: From the Book of Saw |url=http://www.mongrelmedia.com/index.php/filmlink?id=66364d59-dfc5-e911-a98f-0edcbcd33718 |website=[[Mongrel Media]] |date=2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |title=First poster for Saw reboot Spiral is here! |url=https://moviehole.net/first-poster-for-saw-reboot-spiral-is-here/ |author=Editorial Staff |website=Moviehole |date=February 5, 2020 |accessdate=April 18, 2020}}</ref>\n\n== Production ==\n=== Development ===\nAccording to [[Chris Rock]], the origins of ''Spiral: From The Book of Saw'' came from a chance meeting with the head of [[Lionsgate Films|Lionsgate]] at a friend's wedding, and felt doing something in the horror genre would be a new avenue to take his career, though planned to include some comedic elements in the film.<ref>{{cite web | url = https://collider.com/why-chris-rock-made-a-saw-movie/ | title = Chris Rock Explains Why He Made a 'Saw' Movie | first = Adam | last =Chitwood | date = January 13, 2020 | accessdate = January 22, 2020 | work = [[Collider (website)|Collider]] }}</ref>  Rock approached Lionsgate with his ideas of extending the franchise, who became very interested in the concept.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://deadline.com/2019/05/chris-rock-to-reboot-saw-franchise-with-lionsgate-twisted-pictures-1202616185/ |title=Chris Rock To Reboot 'Saw' Franchise With Lionsgate & Twisted Pictures |website=[[Deadline Hollywood]] |publisher=[[Penske Media Corporation]] |first=Anthony |last=D'Alessandro |date=May 16, 2019 |accessdate=August 31, 2019}}</ref> Lionsgate's CEO [[Joe Drake (producer)|Joe Drake]] said that Rock's idea was \"completely reverential to the legacy of the material while reinvigorating the brand with his wit, creative vision and passion for this classic horror franchise\".<ref name=\"announce\"/> By January 2018, industry rumors had said that Lionsgate had begun discussions of a ninth ''Saw'' film, for which [[The Spierig Brothers]] would not be returning.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://screenrant.com/saw-9-jigsaw-sequel/ |title='Saw 9' Conversation is Reportedly Happening |last=Stephens |first=David |website=[[Screen Rant]] |publisher=Valnet, Inc. |date=January 16, 2018 |accessdate=July 8, 2019}}</ref> By April 2018, [[Twisted Pictures]] was reported to be developing a sequel with ''[[Jigsaw (2017 film)|Jigsaw]]'' writers [[Josh Stolberg]] and Peter Goldfinger.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://bloody-disgusting.com/movie/3491755/jigsaw-writers-currently-working-next-saw-exclusive/ |title='Jigsaw' Writers Are Currently Working On Next 'Saw' [Exclusive] |last=Miska |first=Brad |website=[[Bloody Disgusting]] |date=April 3, 2018 |accessdate=July 8, 2019}}</ref>\n\nOn May 16, 2019, the film was officially in production.<ref name=\"announce\"/> Former series director [[Darren Lynn Bousman]] returned to helm the film, along with series veterans [[Mark Burg]] and [[Oren Koules]] as producers. Rock was involved as an executive producer, in addition to writing the story treatment. Joining Rock as executive producers included the original ''[[Saw (2004 film)|Saw]]'' creators [[James Wan]] and [[Leigh Whannell]], along with Daniel Heffner.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://bloody-disgusting.com/movie/3561412/saw-reimagined-chris-rock-darren-bousman-returning-direct/ |title='Saw' Being Reimagined by Chris Rock with Darren Bousman Returning to Direct! |first=Brad |last=Miska |website=[[Bloody Disgusting]] |date=May 16, 2019 |accessdate=August 31, 2019}}</ref> Stolberg and Goldfinger were affirmed as scriptwriters.<ref name=\"announce\"/> With the announcement, Rock stated, \"I've been a fan of ''Saw'' since the first film in 2004. I am excited by the opportunity to take this to a really intense and twisted new place.\"<ref name=\"announce\">{{cite web | url = https://variety.com/2019/film/news/chris-rock-saw-spinoff-1203216731/ | title = Chris Rock Rebooting 'Saw' Franchise With Lionsgate | first=  Dave | last =  McNary | date = May 16, 2019 | accessdate = July 8, 2019 | work = [[Variety (magazine)|Variety]] | publisher = [[Penske Media Corporation]] }}</ref> Burg and Koules said that Rock's treatment of ''Saw'' was comparable to what [[Eddie Murphy]] had done for [[buddy cop film]]s in ''[[48 Hrs.]]'', giving the ''Saw'' series a \"completely fresh perspective\".<ref name=\"announce\"/> Stolberg later confirmed that the ninth installment will exist in the same canon as the previous eight films, and will not be a reboot, nor will it be a direct sequel to ''Jigsaw''.<ref>{{cite web | url = https://www.digitalspy.com/movies/a28205256/saw-movie-reboot-timeline-confirmed/ | title = How 'Saw' reboot fits in with the series timeline | first= Dan | last = Seddon | date = July 8, 2019 | accessdate = July 8, 2019 | work = [[Digital Spy]] | publisher = [[Hearst Communications]]}}</ref>\n\n=== Filming ===\nOn July 8, 2019, filming commenced in [[Toronto]] under the working title of ''The Organ Donor''. Rock, [[Samuel L. Jackson]], [[Max Minghella]] and [[Marisol Nichols]] were announced to be starring in the film.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://variety.com/2019/film/news/samuel-l-jackson-chris-rock-saw-movie-1203260924/ |title=Samuel L. Jackson to Star in Chris Rock's 'Saw' Reboot |last=McNary |first=Dave |date=July 8, 2019 |website=[[Variety (magazine)|Variety]] |publisher=[[Penske Media Corporation]] |accessdate=July 8, 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://screenrant.com/saw-9-movie-filming-start/ |title=New 'Saw' Movie Set To Start Filming This Month |website=[[Screen Rant]] |publisher=Valnet, Inc. |first=Q. V. |last=Hough |date=June 27, 2019 |accessdate=August 31, 2019}}</ref> Lionsgate's CEO Joe Drake stated, \"We think Samuel L. Jackson and Chris Rock along with Max Minghella and Marisol Nichols make this film completely special in the ''Saw'' canon and we can't wait to unleash this unexpected and sinister new story on fans of this franchise. This is next level of ''Saw'' on full tilt.\"<ref>{{cite web |url=https://io9.gizmodo.com/more-like-saw-muel-l-jackson-right-1836185124?IR=T |title=More Like Saw-muel L. Jackson, Right? |last=Lussier |first=Germain |date=July 9, 2019 |website=[[Gizmodo]] |publisher=[[G/O Media]] |accessdate=July 8, 2019}}</ref> On August 28, 2019, filming officially wrapped.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://bloody-disgusting.com/movie/3580945/chris-rocks-new-take-saw-wraps-production/ |title=Chris Rock's New Take on 'Saw' Wraps Production |last=Brad |first=Miska |date=August 28, 2019 |website=[[Bloody Disgusting]] |accessdate=August 29, 2019}}</ref> In February 2020, the [[Motion Picture Association of America]] gave the film an R rating, for \"sequences of grisly bloody violence and torture, pervasive language, some sexual references and brief drug use\".<ref>{{cite web | url=https://www.filmratings.com/Search?filmTitle=spiral&x=0&y=0| title=Spiral (2020) | work=The Classification and Rating Adiministration | publisher=[[Motion Picture Association of America]] | accessdate=February 26, 2020}}</ref>\n\n== Marketing ==\nThe film was known under the working title ''The Organ Donor''<ref>{{cite web |last=Wilhelmi |first=Jack |title=How Does The 'Saw' Reboot Connect To The Original Movies? |url=https://screenrant.com/how-the-saw-reboot-connects-to-original-movies/ |website=[[Screen Rant]] |date=November 24, 2019 |accessdate=March 21, 2020}}</ref> until the name ''Spiral: From the Book of Saw'' was leaked to the press on January 22, 2020, along with [[Mongrel Media]] as the Canadian distributor.<ref>{{cite web |last=Burwick |first=Kevin |title=Bewildering 'Saw 9' Title Allegedly Leaks, But Is It for Real? |url=https://movieweb.com/saw-9-official-title-spiral/ |website=[[MovieWeb]] |date=January 22, 2020 |accessdate=March 21, 2020}}</ref> The first teaser poster and trailer, released on February 5, 2020, confirmed ''Spiral'' as the title of the film.<ref name=\"Patches\">{{cite web |last=Patches |first= Matt |url=https://www.polygon.com/2020/2/5/21124064/spiral-trailer-chris-rock-saw-reboot|title=The 'Spiral' trailer is our first cut of Chris Rock's 'Saw' reboot|website=[[Polygon (website)|Polygon]]|publisher=[[Vox Media]]|date=February 5, 2020|accessdate = February 5, 2020}}</ref>\n\n== Release ==\n''Spiral: From The Book of Saw'' is scheduled to be released in the United States on May 21, 2021, by [[Lionsgate Films|Lionsgate]].<ref name=\"NewDate\" /> The film was originally scheduled to be released on October 23, 2020, but was moved up to May 15, 2020.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://variety.com/2019/film/news/chris-rock-saw-reboot-may-2020-1203275353/ |title=Chris Rock's 'Saw' Reboot Moves Up Five Months to May 2020 |website=[[Variety (magazine)|Variety]] |publisher=[[Penske Media Corporation]] |last=McNary |first=Dave |date=July 22, 2019 |accessdate=July 23, 2019}}</ref> The film was later delayed to its current release date, as a result of the [[COVID-19 pandemic]].<ref name=\"Reschedule\" />\n\n== See also ==\n* [[Impact of the COVID-19 pandemic on cinema]]\n\n== References ==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n== External links ==\n* {{Official website|https://www.lionsgate.com/movies/spiral}}\n* {{IMDb title|10342730|Spiral}}\n* [http://www.mongrelmedia.com/index.php/filmlink?id=66364d59-dfc5-e911-a98f-0edcbcd33718  ''Spiral''] on [[Mongrel Media]]\n\n{{Chris Rock}}\n{{Darren Lynn Bousman}}\n{{Saw}}\n{{Portal bar|Film|Speculative fiction/Horror}}\n\n[[Category:2021 horror films]]\n[[Category:2021 films]]\n[[Category:American films]]\n[[Category:American horror films]]\n[[Category:American sequel films]]\n[[Category:English-language films]]\n[[Category:Films directed by Darren Lynn Bousman]]\n[[Category:Films postponed due to the 2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic]]\n[[Category:Films shot in Toronto]]\n[[Category: